<h1><i class="fa fa-home"></i>Viewing Your Public Home Page</h1>

<ol class="breadcrumb">
	<li><a href="#help"><i class="fa fa-question-circle"></i>Help</a></li>
	<li><a href="#help/creating-profile"><i class="fa fa-user-circle"></i>Creating Your Profile</a></li>
	<li><i class="fa fa-home"></i>Viewing Your Public Home Page</li>
</ol>

<div class="content">
	<p>When you create your <%= application.name %> account, a publicly visible home page is created for you.  Your public home page can be shared with anyone, whether or not they have a <%= application.name %> account. You can use this page to share information about yourself as well as files and photos. </p>

	<ol>
		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-link"></i>Getting a Link to Your Public Home Page</h2>
			<p>To get a link to your public home page, open up your <a href="#help/creating-profile/viewing-profile">User Profile</a> and then go to the "Share" menu and click on "By Link". </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<img class="dropdown menu" src="images/help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page/share-by-link-menu-item@2x.png" />
				<div class="caption">"Share by Link" on the Share Menu</div>
			</div>

			<p>This will open the "Copy Link" dialog box as shown below.</p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page/copy-link-dialog.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Copy Link Dialog Box"><img class="dialog" src="images/help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page/copy-link-dialog.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Copy Link Dialog Box</div>
			</div>

			<p>To copy the link, click on the "Copy Link" button, which will copy the link to your public home page to your clipboard.  Once the link is in your clipboard, you can paste it into an email, web page, social media web site or anywhere that a hyperlink can be shared or viewed. </p>
		</li>

		<li>
			<h2><i class="fa fa-eye"></i>Viewing the Link to Your Public Home Page</h2>
			<p>To view your public home page, click on the "View Link" button on the "Copy Link" dialog box, which will open up your home page in the <a href="#apps/web-browser">Web Browser</a> app. </p>

			<div class="figure">
				<a href="images/help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page/public-home-page.png" target="_blank" class="lightbox" title="Your Public Home Page"><img src="images/help/creating-profile/viewing-home-page/public-home-page.png" /></a>
				<div class="caption">Your Public Home Page</div>
			</div>
		</li>
	</ol>
</div>